# YOLOv8 Crowd Estimation Module

This report describes the architecture, implementation, and integration of the **Crowd Estimation Module** into the **AI Command Center for Bengaluru Traffic Police** project for the Flipkart Gridlock Hackathon.

---

## 1. System Architecture

The newly integrated Crowd Estimation Module interfaces directly with CCTV feeds (images or videos) using **ultralytics YOLOv8** for human detection. The estimated pedestrian count is mapped to crowd density categories, which dynamically scale resource allocation recommendations and update the overall traffic congestion risk.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[CCTV Image / Video Upload] --> B[YOLOv8 Object Detector]
    B -->|Filter Class 0: person| C[Pedestrian Count]
    C --> D[Density Categorization]
    D -->|Low / Medium / High / Extreme| E[Dynamic Resource Engine]
    E -->|Scale Officers & Barricades| F[Updated Command Dashboard]
    E -->|Update Congestion Risk| F
```

---

